data.value:
Boltzman Constant = (0.5 * Mass * Root Mean Square Velocity) / (1.5 * Temperature) - Cubic Expansitivity of a liquid = (Change in volume) / (Volume at 273 Kelvins * Change in temperature) - Monatomic Internal Energy of a gas = (3/2 * Gas constant per unit mass * Temperature) - Diatomic Internal Energy of a gas = (5/2 * Gas constant per unit mass * Temperature)
Ideal Gases ___________________________________________________________________
Ideal Gas Number of moles = (Pressure * Volume) / (Molar gas constant * Temperature) - Ideal Gas Pressure = (Number of moles * Molar gas constant * Temperature) / Volume - Ideal Gas Temperature = (Pressure * Volume) / (Number of moles * Molar gas constant) - Ideal Gas Volume = (Number of moles * Molar gas constant * Temperature) / Pressure
___________________________________________________________________
Linear Expansitivity of a substance = Expansion / (Original Length * Temperature Rise) - Specific Heat Capacity of a substance = Mass of substance * Specific Heat Capacity of material * Temperature Change - Specific Latent Heat of Vapourization of a substance = Energy required / Mass of material
